items.text: Not to complicated menu make your orders are easy, they even suggest how much you should order. The mezzes are good, but the main course are even better. Go for lamb and prawn!
they changed the brunch menu and the mezza platter is no longer available 😭
The Forgotten Grains Salad is amazing! I can go vegetarian for a day with the melange of textures and flavours in this!
Delightful place that serves great food; a perfect place to spend a lazy afternoon :) Love the moorish touch Chef Bjorn breathed into the food. Must tries: everything lamb and canadian maple bacon.
One of the better brunches in Singapore with creative and interesting food that's also delicious
One of the best, most original and friendliest restaurants in Singapore. The beetroot tzatziki is heavenly as are any of the (constantly changing) bacon dishes.
Everything here is great but try the beetroot, burrata and lamb for starters
Loving the lamb shakshoula. The organic mushrooms were awesome as well.
Great mezes and nice Australian wine
Order the mezze plate for any meal of the day! Great mix of all the good stuff.
Love the mezzes and the burrata. Lamb shoulder is also decent. Definitely a place to try if u haven't and to return to. Reservations recommended.
Lamb shakshouka is absolutely to die for! The scrambled eggs & bacon is a bit disappointing due to the tough bacon. Portion sizes are huge so be prepared of you're thinking of dessert
Good ambience. The 3 set mezze platter is quite worth it to share. Try the labna, or the walnut dip if you want a sweet starter. They do run out of items if you come too late.
Super cadre
I was seated at an outdoor table that blocked one of two exit areas, even if there were other vacant tables. Most unpleasant to be eating while people bump your table on their way out or to the loo.
Great atmosphere & delicious food. The hummus is a must order! Don't be shocked when the bill comes though, all the little dishes add up to make quite a pricey meal!
get the mezza platter if you want something different!
Date pudding is a must-try!
Nice place destroyed by a rather rude boss who questioned why we entered his cafe as though we were gonna rob him.
Brunch till 4pm on weekends and Dinner serves till 11pm on weeknights. Good romantic/chill spot. A hidden gem. :)
Great review - http://www.ladyironchef.com/2011/03/best-cafes-singapore/
One of the best kept secrets in Singapore - such a great place!
Pretty much anything you order is awesome.
Please make your reservation by phone a few days in advance to prevent disappointment of no seats available!
everything we ate was fantastic. especially the burrata.
Order anything lamb here. Lamb is good. Baaaaaaaaa.
Excellent! Try the beetroot and carrot curry mezze. For share plates go for the cauliflower and squid. None of these will disappoint! Enjoy.
Love their hummus!
Fried cauliflower with smoked egg and Israeli salad, hummous and labneh -- fantastic (and gluten-free if you omit the pita). Great vibe and food, slow service.
Seems like the Bacon chop dish wasn't  as good as before, :(
Good food and groovy music. Great place to bring a group & share food - great atmosphere.
It's a blessing to be able to have a meal, what more with such an enjoyable one at artichoke. Beetroot tzatziki, burnt asparagus, samke harra (seared salmon), chargrilled squid were simply fantastic
Pretty busy. Outdoor seating not ideal especially with kids
Overrated place, unfriendly staff
Went back after a long time, food not as good, had to send eggs back because they were too salty, but were pretty much the same second time around, not worth the price you pay....
Opening Hrs: No lunch; it's a dinner place. Tue–Sat: 6:30pm-11pm (last order 9:45pm)- Brunch on Sat & Sun: 11:30am-4pm (last order 2:45pm)- Closed on Mon
Maybe the best meal we had in Singapore, went there twice in 4 days. Their prawns and hummus were great for dinner. Their shakshouka and fried chicken are must orders for brunch.
The Bacon & eggs is Legit
Decent place with a nice outside sitting area. They changed the menu a few months ago and it's not so brunchy anymore. But the food is still good.
Vege-heaven! The mushroom scrambled egg with grilled tomatoes and rocket is highly recommended.
The cauliflower dish is awesome .. so are the desserts !!
The desserts were pretty awesome
When you come to the cafe 110 times, this is direct evidence that here is cool👍Chocolate Cake ($7,50) and coffee are great 👏
Not sure what the fuss is all about. The menu is extremely limited and don't know why it's called a brunch place. Much better places nearby
Muhammara dip: Luv it! It's got a sweet/sour aftertaste. Njoyed d crunchiness of diced onion bits dat gave some fizz on da tongue!
love the sticky date pudding! absolutely divine :)
Great atmosphere and friendly / attentive service. The food was a bit disappointing after all the good things I'd heard. But the baked broccoli was delicious.
MezZe platter and lamb shakshoula FTW
Fuck yeah. Great spot. Will be back.
Excellent food and vibe, seating outdoors and indoors.
Burrata and lamb shaksuka excellent!
Try the bbq bacon chop. To die for!
Must order the peanut butter gelato. Damn!
Over rated, food n coffee was mediocre. Ordered the pork and I think it was slightly uncooked. Tummy upset.
Try the Cookie Pie for dessert! It's cookie dough that's a bit savory, freshly baked, topped with vanilla ice cream. Surprisingly lovely.
"Save water drink wine."
Burnt asparagus and squid.
Lamb and edamame goat cheese mezze. Delicious!
Good food, small portions, poor service.
I've been here 4 times & have tried 14 dishes. LOVED: 1) Date Pudding (Sticky) 2) Smoked Oyster Taramasalata 3) Soft Scrambled Eggs, Thick Cut Maple Bacon Chop. See Top 10 dishes on Foodmento:
Place with some character.. Good selection of food, dessert.. decent wines.. Casual but quiet ambience.. Love the place
everything. hummus, pita bread (it's so soft and yummy), brussel sprouts, fancy fish sticks (forget the name)
Self destruction was yummy but heavy! Eat it only if you're starving and even then, you might not be able to finish it!
Cuisine: Middle Eastern/Moorish-inspired. Arabic bread, dips, tahini dressing, haloumi cheese. U get d drift :-)
So not with it
Unmissable brunch spot on Sunday in Singapore. Chilled out vibes and great food
Awesome huevos rancheros
A lot of middle eastern-inspired brunch items like eggs with haloumi cheese. Portion is generous. Staff is friendly but slow. Reservation is needed for a large group. Overall it's a great place.
Artichoke is a labour of love and you can tell. Each dish has character, the service is engaging enough that I go on my own knowing I'll have fun. The sharing dish specials are always fantastic.
Coffee next door at Overdoughs is better, but more expensive. But the food here is great! Love the lamb shakshouka I had! Recommended!
Their eggs and bacon is on another level.
Food is great, and excellent value for money (even though some may complain about portion size, it wasn't an issue for me). As for the beers, "Fucking Hell" is a great name but a terrible beer.
Absolutely hidden gem in Waterloo st. Would be better if serving staffs were more attentive. Love their brunch mezze assorting with various dishes!
and just when were about to go in I get a "but you have to leave by 1215" $20 for scrambled eggs!? Sorry. Stuck up and offensive tones don't make for return business. Or any business since we left.
Try the The Lambgasm
The whole roasted chicken marinated with ras el hanout has made it onto the Mediterranean menu ($56).There is an enticing weekend brunch – although the prices seem a bit steep, no?
Crispy whitebait: By itself, forgettable. But dip in2 d black sesame tahini aioli & dis little fish comes alive. Lovely snack 2 share
Had honeyed yogurt with rhubarb and roasted nuts...absolutely to die for!
Try the pork chop w celery root mash. Rocks!
Cauliflower salad is great !
Roasted pork belly: Plain. Except for d crackling crispy skin, it's a very plain-looking, plain-tasting dish. Couldn't even taste d herbed pork sauce :-(
Food is really good 😋
Brunch!! Lamb short ribs are to die for and Spanish Serrano Jamon! Meat candy with maple syrup... Yumz!
Prawns are absolutely amazing.
Smoked salmon pancake and lamb shakshouka for brunch. Nice vibes
The Bacon & Eggs is LEGIT!
Popular place. Small, good menu. Probably wouldn't order the haloumi cheese (too salty) or bacon chop (weird) again. Doesn't open until 11.30am (on a Sunday at least)
Have been here three times. First two times fried chicken and slow cooked lamb were excellent. Third time the food was so-so and vibe was that they were too cool for customers. Need reservations.
Try the broccoli! It's v v good!
delicious brunch w/ a Mexican twist (nachos, avocado, corn) & halloumi. latte was a lil watery but scrumptious food made up 4 it. love the ambience & menu offering. will return again 4 sure
Mains are ok but mezze is the real star. Some of the best hummus & labneh I've had since leaving the MidEast. Staff camped on laptop at the bar in full view is sloppy. Front of house isn't an office.
Mezze platter was good but the rest of the food was overpriced
Middle eastern cuisine + drinks
My dessert making eyes to me. 😍 average bill 40-50$. No alcohol 😗
One of my fav restaurants in Singapore. Go for the Harisa prawns
The date dessert is devil-licious!
Seasonal menu.
The feta burratta on turkish bread 👍
Fish roe, raw tuna, crispy chicken skin- enough said.
This is supposed to be s middle eastern restaurant yet nothing on the menu was middle eastern. Very dissatisfied.

I think,how long will exist this cafe, so I'll be here for a long time to come!There are good cuisine,atmosphere & staff. My favorite dishes Feta Burrate-22$;Skillet Prawns-36$;Falafel-18$.Bill 2-100$

Food is good but service is bad, the guy who looks like he is the manager is rude, asked him simple question, how long is the wait, his answer was I don't know there are people ahead of u, gee thanks!
Nice ambience and friendly staff. Grow their own veggies (it seems). The mezze platter is great. Perfect for brunch / lunch / meetings.
Love the pork belly & roast chicken dishes. Really filling for 2 pax. Pita bread was a bit thick but goes well with hummus. Was delighted by yoghurt that was served w the chicken - extra kick to it!
Great menu!
Burrata was good, with pomegranate on top. Salmon dish is new but very flavorful with the green pea sauce. Turkish bread and pita bread are both good.
Their feta buratta is to die for!
Be early for brunch or tea :) desserts are great for sharing.
